<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 9. Fainia elongata (Bezzi, 1908). Male terminalia (BMSA-BECE 03371) A, B epandrial complex in dorsal (A) and lateral (B) view C-E phallus in dorsal (C), lateral (D) and ventral (E) view F sternite 5 in ventral view and G postgonite (upper) and pregonite in lateral-external view (G). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." , "Figure 12. Fainia kirinyaga Lehrer, 2007 b holotype (SMNHTAU (TAUI) 318989) male terminalia A, B epandrial complex in dorsal (A) and lateral (B) view C-E phallus in dorsal (C), lateral (D) and ventral (E) view F sternite 5 in ventral view and G postgonite (upper) and pregonite lateral-internal view (G) H Fainia inexpectata Zumpt, 1973 details of medial lobe tear (red circle) of the sternite 5 in ventral view. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." , "Figure 10. Fainia inexpectata Zumpt, 1973. General body views of male (MZSUR) and female (paratype NMSA DIP 61575) A, C, E, G, I, J male A head in frontal view C head in lateral view E abdomen in dorsal view G thorax in dorsal view I hind tibia with two anterodorsal setae (arrows) J lateral habitus and labels B, D, F, H, K female B head in frontal view D head in lateral view F abdomen in dorsal view H thorax in dorsal view K lateral habitus and labels. Scale bars: 2 mm." , "Figure 11. Fainia inexpectata Zumpt, 1973. Male terminalia (MZSUR) A, B epandrial complex in dorsal (A) and lateral (B) view C-E phallus in dorsal (C), lateral (D) and ventral (E) view F sternite 5 in ventral view and G postgonite (upper) and pregonite in lateral-internal view (G). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." , "Figure 13. Fainia kirinyaga Lehrer, 2007 b holotype (SMNHTAU (TAUI) 318989), Fainia sambura Lehrer, 2008 holotype (SMNHTAU (TAUI) 318989) and Fainia kagerana Lehrer, 2007 a nom. nud. (SMNHTAU (TAUI) 318990) general body and heads views A, D, G F. kirinyaga dorsal habitus view (A), lateral habitus view (D) and head frontal view (G) B, F, H Fainia sambura dorsal habitus view (B), lateral habitus view (F) and head frontal view (H) C, E, I Fainia kagerana nom. nud. dorsal habitus view (C), lateral habitus view (E) and head frontal view (I). Scale bars: 2 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/534850" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/534851" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/534848" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/534849" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/534852" .

